“Clothing accessories” or “equipment” means incidental items worn on the person or in conjunction with “clothing.” “Clothing accessories or equipment” are mutually exclusive of and may be taxed differently than apparel within the definition of “clothing,” “sport or recreational equipment,” and “protective equipment.” The following list contains examples and is not intended to be an all-inclusive list. “Clothing accessories or equipment” shall include:
(A) briefcases;
(B) cosmetics;
(C) hair notions, including barrettes, hair bows, and hair nets;
(D) handbags;
(E) handkerchiefs;
(F) jewelry;
(G) sunglasses, nonprescription;
(H) umbrellas;
(I) wallets;
(J) watches; and
(K) wigs and hairpieces.

